RIYADH: Saudi Ministry of Environment, Water and Agriculture has called for investments in four agricultural projects aimed at enhancing the Kingdomâ€™s food security. The projects in Makkah, Qassim and Jazan seek to produce high quality vegetables and fruits, Al-Eqtisadiah reported. The project also include a green house in Al-Qassim, sheep breeding and fattening in Jazan, and the establishment of a horse veterinary hospital in Makkah Al-Mukarramah.